(12, 4, 6, 'Golden Pothos', 'Plantopia', 3100, 3750, '<ul><li><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: GlacialRegular; font-size: 17px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;\">The golden pothos is the best plant for driving out bad vibes while welcoming in good ones. What else could you ask for? This plant has it all! The energy of dark corners, cabinets, and other office areas can be brightened and revitalized by placing this plant there.</span></li></ul>', 'Golden Pothos 1.jpg', 'Golden Pothos 2.png', 'Golden Pothos 3.jpg', 100, 'In Stock', '2017-02-04 04:28:17', ''),
(13, 4, 6, 'Peace Lily', 'Plantopia', 14999, 18250, '<div><ul><li><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: GlacialRegular; margin-bottom: 1rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 17px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 25px; letter-spacing: 0.2px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41);\">Some succulents aren’t good for feng shui, but the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unbeleafable.ph/product/jade-plant\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(82, 148, 133); text-decoration-line: underline; transition: 0.35s ease-in-out; font-weight: 900;\">jade plant</a>&nbsp;is not one of them. Its soft, coin-shaped leaf segments are known to bring good fortune and financial success to its owner.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: GlacialRegular; margin-bottom: 1rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 17px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 25px; letter-spacing: 0.2px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41);\">Put it where it will get lots of light, such as the “wealth corner” of your desk or office. Never allow a jade plant to sit in standing water, and only pot in soil that drains well.</p></li></ul></div>', 'Peace Lily 1.jpg', 'Peace Lily 2.jpg', 'Peace Lily 3.jpg', 300, 'In Stock', '2017-02-04 04:30:24', ''),
(14, 4, 6, 'Ficus Ginseng Plant', 'Plantopia', 5099, 6299, '<div><ul><li><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: GlacialRegular; margin-bottom: 1rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 17px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 25px; letter-spacing: 0.2px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41);\">Money doesn’t grow with trees, but&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unbeleafable.ph/product/money-tree\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(82, 148, 133); text-decoration-line: underline; transition: 0.35s ease-in-out; font-weight: 900;\">money trees</a>&nbsp;are used in feng shui to bring financial prosperity! They’re visually pleasing and simple to cultivate in an office setting. This plant can also be given to employees to reward and honor the work that they do. In turn, it will bring them good luck as well.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: GlacialRegular; margin-bottom: 1rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 17px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 25px; letter-spacing: 0.2px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41);\">Place this plant in the office’s wealthiest area to attract clients. A money tree needs warm, filtered sunshine; prefers equally moist soil. It is also not fond of drafts.</p></li></ul></div>', 'Ficus Ginseng Plant 2.avif', 'Ficus Ginseng Plant 1.avif', 'Ficus Ginseng Plant 3.jpg', 0, 'In Stock', '2017-02-04 04:32:15', ''),
